title: GOP Retains House Seat on Long Island, a Swing-District Battleground
description: Representative Andrew Garbarino defended his seat for the Republicans, who also held late leads in three other Long Island House races.
dc:creator: Liam Stack
media:credit: Johnny Milano for The New York Times
media:description: Representative Andrew Garbarino, a Republican and the lone incumbent running among the four House races on Long Island, won his race.
